            <commentid>12360</commentid>
            <who name="Helder Magalhães">helder.magalhaes</who>
            <bug_when>2009-09-16 15:50:36 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>(In reply to comment #0)
&gt; This should be quite easily todo

Yes, once one figures out intervention is needed... ;-)

The changes are minimal, but affect both the tool set and the client code.


&gt; [...] and should not have side effects for most users.

This is where I&#39;m not quite sure about. Although it&#39;s not a typical use-case, one may want to edit/view the files, and the &quot;.json&quot; extension is typically not registered with any editor, while the &quot;.js&quot; typically is. Apart from this, and given this set of files is not supposed to be edited by users (it&#39;s content generated automatically), I&#39;d say the changes are safe to apply. :-)</thetext>
          </long_desc>
